  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, cricket moments with friends are the best, the shouting, the joy. Any recent games that brought back those feelings?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Last weekend, me and my friends played a small match. We were all in our 30s but still had so much fun. One ball hit the stumps — super exciting! It felt like old times."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds fun. Playing with friends always brings back good memories. What made that ball so exciting?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The bowler ran in fast, I focused on the ball — *whiz* — and just as he released, I saw the spin. I waited, waited... then *thwack*! I hit it straight, and it crashed into the stumps. The guy on strike didn't even move. All of us jumped up — priceless moment."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That was a great play. Seeing the spin and timing the shot perfectly takes skill. Did you all celebrate with something special after the match?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "We went to a small diner nearby and ordered a lot of chaat and cold drinks. It’s our usual post-match routine. We laughed a lot, replayed the moments — especially my \"stump crasher\" — and even ordered a few shots of *tamarind soda* to toast. Simple, but perfect."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds like a perfect way to wind down. Tamarind soda with chaat, such a fun combo. What’s your go to chaat in a situation like that?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My favorite is *dahi puri*. The mix of tangy tamarind water, spicy chaat masala, and the cool yogurt — it just hits right after a hot game. Sometimes we add some sev and onions on top. Simple, but so satisfying."
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds delicious. The tangy and spicy mix must balance the excitement of the game. Do you try new chaat recipes often, or stick to the classics?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Mostly stick to classics — they’re reliable after a game. But once in a while, we try something new, like *pani puri with guava pani* or *aloo tikki with mint chutney*. Keeps things interesting, but not too much! I should head off now — gotta prep for a meeting. Talk to you later!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right, dahi puri is a classic for a reason. Those new twists sound fun to try. Let me know how your meeting goes, talk to you soon!"
    }
  ],
